						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍapa,</hi> Tiruvālanduṟaiyār temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 12: 983 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 90 sheep for maintaining a perpetual lamp to god Mahādēva at Śiṟupaḻuvūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam,</hi> in Kuṉṟak-kūṟṟam by Madhurāntakaṉ, son of Aḍigaḷ Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyar for the merit of Vīrakali Araṅgaṉ, a native of Mudukuḍi in Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam who was killed in a fight with Mādēvaḍigaḷ.</p>						

						</summary>
